ral en una serie de textos coloniales paradigmáticos de la historia cultural latinoamericana que incluyen relaciones de conquista, obras de teatro imperial, relatos etnográficos, planes de gobierno y control de la población, novelas e historiografías de autores como Bernal Díaz del Castillo, Álvar Núñez Cabeza de Vaca, Bartolomé de las Casas, Michael de Carvajal, sor Juana Inés de la Cruz, José de Anchieta, Antônio Vieira, Eligio Ancona y Oswaldo Costa, entre otros.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2020z9783110689631oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396456818240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783964568182423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783964568182.jpg  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-207-IBVb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020